commands.name: az networkcloud kubernetescluster feature create
commands.summary: Create a new Kubernetes cluster feature or update properties of the Kubernetes cluster feature if it exists.
commands.syntax:
az networkcloud kubernetescluster feature create --feature-name
                                                 --kc-name
                                                 --resource-group
                                                 [--location]
                                                 [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                                 [--options]
                                                 [--tags]
examples: az networkcloud kubernetescluster feature create --name "featureName" --kubernetes-cluster-name "kubernetesClusterName" --resource-group "resourceGroupName" --location "location" --tags key1="myvalue1" key2="myvalue2"

commands.name: az networkcloud kubernetescluster feature delete
commands.summary: Delete the provided Kubernetes cluster feature.
commands.syntax:
az networkcloud kubernetescluster feature delete [--feature-name]
                                                 [--ids]
                                                 [--kc-name]
                                                 [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                                 [--resource-group]
                                                 [--subscription]
                                                 [--yes]

commands.name: az networkcloud kubernetescluster feature list
commands.summary: List a list of features for the provided Kubernetes cluster.

commands.name: az networkcloud kubernetescluster feature show
commands.summary: Get properties of the provided the Kubernetes cluster feature.

commands.name: az networkcloud kubernetescluster feature update
commands.summary: Update properties of the provided Kubernetes cluster feature.
commands.syntax:
az networkcloud kubernetescluster feature update [--feature-name]
                                                 [--ids]
                                                 [--kc-name]
                                                 [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                                 [--resource-group]
                                                 [--subscription]
                                                 [--tags]
examples: az networkcloud kubernetescluster feature update --name "featureName" --kubernetes-cluster-name "kubernetesClusterName" --resource-group "resourceGroupName" --tags key1="myvalue1" key2="myvalue2"

commands.name: az networkcloud kubernetescluster feature wait
commands.summary: Place the CLI in a waiting state until a condition is met.
